<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
When describing 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schultes, JA" journalOrPublisher="Stuttgardtiae, Sumtibus J. G. Cottae" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B94" refString="Schultes, JA, Schultes, JH, 1830. Caroli a Linné equitis Systema vegetabilium secundum classes, ordines, genera, species; cum characteribus, differentiis et synonymiis, vol. 7, part 2. Stuttgardtiae, Sumtibus J.G. Cottae" title="Caroli a Linne ́ equitis Systema vegetabilium secundum classes, ordines, genera, species; cum characteribus, differentiis et synonymiis, vol. 7, part 2." year="1830">Schultes and Schultes (1830)</bibRefCitation>
mention that their new species is based in Martius specimens from Brazil. However, the author makes no mention in which herbarium the specimens are housed or their 
<normalizedToken originalValue="collectors’">collectors'</normalizedToken>
numbers. While consulting the specimens at M, we came across two 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martius’">Martius'</normalizedToken>
specimens (i.e. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 14</emphasis>
M0242238; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 16</emphasis>
M0242244) that matched the protologue of 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both specimens were annotated in Martius handwriting and were probably analysed by Schultes. Since the specimen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 14</emphasis>
(M0242238) is a more complete collection, when compared with 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 16</emphasis>
(M0242244), which is composed of two detached leaves and two inflorescences, it is selected by us as the lectotype for 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="taxonomical notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Taxonomical notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Pontederia ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered by most authors and online databases as either a variety (
<bibRefCitation author="Dubs, B" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B26" refString="Dubs, B, 1998. Prodromus Florae Matogrossensis, Series B, No. 3. Betrona-Verlag." title="Prodromus Florae Matogrossensis, Series B, No. 3. Betrona-Verlag." year="1998">Dubs 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) or a synonym (
<bibRefCitation author="Schulz, AG" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="45 - 87" refId="B95" refString="Schulz, AG, 1942. Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina. Darwiniana 6 (1): 45 - 87" title="Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina." volume="6" year="1942">Schulz 1942</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. cordata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nonetheless, both morphologically and phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much more similar to 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. sagittata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="sagittata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. sagittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to its pubescent inflorescence main axis and fruits with sinuate ridges. Thus, 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here re-established, being also part of the 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. cordata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
